{
  "stem": "18770.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Gestapo has already been to the house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They are beginning to sort of, I guess, figure out who's Jewish and who isn't.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, what they're going to do with it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "German soldiers have been coming into the house to requisition things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "One time, they come into the house and my grandmother takes some zloty-- you know, Polish currency-- maybe the equivalent of $5,000 or $10,000 that she had taken with her, and wrapping it up in rags-- wet rags-- and putting it into the stove so they won't look there and won't find it.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they don't find it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They leave and she opens the stove and the whole thing is burnt to a crisp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] It's that kind of a time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Anyway, the governess leaves, and I'm very sick.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There's-- so the family at this point splits up into smaller groups.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We know we're not going to be able to get out of there in one group, and so the men go-- three or four of the men-- go in one group, some of the aunts and uncles with their children go in another group.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Finally, when I'm better, we leave Chelm with-- that's my, my aunt, my cousin who's my age, and my mother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember two things from that exodus.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "One is that we were stopped at some point by-- at a German-- by German soldiers at a checkpoint.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we're in a wagon.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We're being ferried out of there-- ferried sounds like on a boat, but I mean we're being taken out of there in like one of those wagons with a-- hay wagon.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We're paying for that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a kind of Underground Railroad that's being run by Jews, I guess, and non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
